{
  "category": "productivity",
  "count": 111,
  "quotes": [
    {
      "text": "Productivity is never an accident. It is always the result of commitment to excellence, intelligent planning, and focused effort.",
      "author": "Paul J. Meyer",
      "author_slug": "meyer",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "planning",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "meyer-productivity-is-never-an",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The key is not to prioritize what's on your schedule, but to schedule your priorities.",
      "author": "Stephen Covey",
      "author_slug": "covey",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "priorities",
        "planning"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "covey-the-key-is-not",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Productivity is doing more of what matters. Not doing more things.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "focus",
        "priorities"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-productivity-is-doing-more",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your to-do list isn't a productivity tool. It's a guilt collection. Delete it and do the one thing that matters.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "todo",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-your-todo-list-isnt",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The most productive people aren't the ones who do the most. They're the ones who say no the most.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "focus",
        "saying-no"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-most-productive-people",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Meetings are where minutes are kept and hours are lost.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "meetings",
        "waste"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-meetings-are-where-minutes",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If your calendar is full, you're not productive. You're just busy. There's a difference.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "calendar",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-your-calendar-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best productivity hack is a deadline. The second best is consequences.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deadlines",
        "motivation"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-productivity-hack",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "You don't need a second monitor. You need fewer tabs.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "setup",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-you-dont-need-a",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The Pomodoro Technique is great until you enter flow state and your timer interrupts you to take a break you didn't need.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "pomodoro",
        "flow-state"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-the-pomodoro-technique-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Inbox Zero is a lie. The goal isn't zero emails. It's zero emails that matter.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "email",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-inbox-zero-is-a",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Every time management introduces a new 'productivity tool,' productivity drops by 30% while everyone learns it, then returns to baseline.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "tools",
        "management"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 4,
      "id": "based-every-time-management-introduces",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Batch your shallow work. Protect your deep work. Ignore everything else.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deep-work",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-batch-your-shallow-work",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to get something done is to begin. Not to plan. Not to research. Not to optimize. Begin.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "action",
        "beginning"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Multitasking is a myth. You're just switching between tasks poorly and calling it efficiency.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "multitasking",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-multitasking-is-a-myth",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best note-taking system is the one you actually use. Not the one you spend 47 hours setting up.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "notes",
        "tools"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-the-best-notetaking-system",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Burnout isn't caused by working too hard. It's caused by working too hard on things that don't matter.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "burnout",
        "meaning"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-burnout-isnt-caused-by",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The most productive thing you can do today is delete half your to-do list.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "todo",
        "simplification"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-the-most-productive-thing",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your morning routine doesn't matter if your evening routine is doomscrolling until 2 AM.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "morning-routine",
        "sleep"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-your-morning-routine-doesnt",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Hustle culture is just exploitation with better marketing.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "hustle",
        "burnout"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 5,
      "id": "based-hustle-culture-is-just",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The 5 AM club only works if you go to bed at 9 PM. Most people who join it just lose 2 hours of sleep and call it discipline.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "morning-routine",
        "sleep"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 4,
      "id": "based-the-5-am-club",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Done is better than perfect. But also: good is better than done-but-broken.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "shipping",
        "quality"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-done-is-better-than",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If it takes less than 2 minutes, do it now. If it takes less than 2 hours, do it today. If it takes longer, schedule it and then don't schedule it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "gtd",
        "execution"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-if-it-takes-less",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Time management is really just priority management. If everything is a priority, nothing is.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "priorities",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-time-management-is-really",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The real productivity hack is caring less about productivity hacks and more about the work.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "meta",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-the-real-productivity-hack",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best investment you can make is in yourself. The second best is in tools that save you time. The worst is in courses that save you nothing.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "investment",
        "learning"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-the-best-investment-you",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to get more done is to stop doing things that don't matter. It sounds obvious. It isn't.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "focus",
        "elimination"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-427",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your brain is a browser with too many tabs open. Close some before you crash.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "focus",
        "overload"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-your-brain-is-a",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best investment in productivity is sleep. Not coffee, not apps, not standing desks. Sleep.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "sleep",
        "health"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-investment-in",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If you can't do it in 2 hours, you can't do it today. Break it down or give up.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "breaking-down",
        "execution"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-you-cant-do",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best meetings are the ones that don't happen. The second best are the ones that end early.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "meetings",
        "efficiency"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-the-best-meetings-are",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Discipline is choosing between what you want now and what you want most. Most people choose now.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "discipline",
        "delayed-gratification"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-discipline-is-choosing-between",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The most productive 2 hours of your day are the ones where you're not checking notifications.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "notifications",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-most-productive-2",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If you're reading productivity books instead of doing the work, you're procrastinating with extra steps.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "procrastination",
        "action"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-if-youre-reading-productivity",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time management trick is realizing you can't manage time. You can only manage yourself.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "time-management",
        "self-management"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-management",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your calendar reflects your priorities. If it doesn't, you don't have priorities — you have wishes.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "calendar",
        "priorities"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-your-calendar-reflects-your",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best career advice is: nobody is coming to save you. You have to build your own thing.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "career",
        "self-reliance"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-career-advice",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Work-life balance is a myth. What matters is work-life integration — doing work you don't need to escape from.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "work-life",
        "balance"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-worklife-balance-is-a",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The hardest part of remote work isn't productivity. It's knowing when to stop.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "remote-work",
        "boundaries"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-hardest-part-of-484",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your first job teaches you skills. Your second teaches you politics. Your third teaches you which one matters more.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "career",
        "politics"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-your-first-job-teaches",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to get promoted is to do the job you want, not the job you have. But don't do it for free.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "career",
        "promotion"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-486",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Side projects are the best career insurance. They prove you can build things, not just talk about them.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "indie-hacker"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "side-projects",
        "career"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-side-projects-are-the-487",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to negotiate your salary is when you don't need the job. The worst is when you desperately do.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "salary",
        "negotiation"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-to-488",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your GitHub profile is your resume. If it's empty, so is your argument for why you're a good developer.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "github",
        "resume"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-your-github-profile-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Burnout isn't a badge of honor. It's a sign you're doing something wrong. Rest is productive.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "burnout",
        "rest"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-burnout-isnt-a-badge",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to learn is to teach. The best way to teach is to build something that explains itself.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "learning",
        "teaching"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-491",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Imposter syndrome means you're in the right room. If you're the smartest person in the room, you're in the wrong room.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "imposter-syndrome",
        "growth"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-imposter-syndrome-means-youre",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to update your resume is when you don't need one. The second best is when you're too late.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "resume",
        "career"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-to-493",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your LinkedIn feed is just Twitter for people who think they're too professional for Twitter.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "shitpost"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "linkedin",
        "social-media"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-your-linkedin-feed-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to get better at coding is to code. Not to watch tutorials. Not to read books. To code.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "learning",
        "practice"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-495",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best habit is the one you actually maintain. Not the one that looks best on paper.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "habits",
        "realism"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-habit-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "You don't need a perfect morning routine. You need a routine that doesn't make you hate mornings.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "routine",
        "realism"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-you-dont-need-a-572",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best investment is in yourself. The best return is confidence.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "investment",
        "confidence"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "based-the-best-investment-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Knowledge is power. Applied knowledge is superpower. Hoarded knowledge is a hoarder.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "knowledge",
        "application"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-knowledge-is-power-applied",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to start that thing you've been putting off is exactly now.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "procrastination",
        "action"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-to-575",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If you're waiting for motivation, you'll be waiting forever. Motivation follows action, not the other way around.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "motivation",
        "action"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-youre-waiting-for",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to predict your future is to create it. Start today.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "future",
        "action"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-577",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your attention is your most valuable resource. Spend it like you'd spend your last dollar.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "attention",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-attention-is-your",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to manage stress is to eliminate the source. If you can't eliminate it, change your relationship with it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "stress",
        "management"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-579",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Done is better than perfect. Shipped is better than done. Revenue is better than shipped.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "shipping",
        "priorities"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-done-is-better-than-580",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The most productive people aren't busy. They're focused. Busy is noise. Focus is signal.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "focus",
        "busyness"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-most-productive-people-581",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If it's not on your calendar, it doesn't exist. Dreams without deadlines are just fantasies.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "calendar",
        "deadlines"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-its-not-on",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to get more done is to do less. Say no to the mediocre so you can say yes to the excellent.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "saying-no",
        "excellence"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-583",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "You can't pour from an empty cup. Fill yours first.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "self-care",
        "energy"
      ],
      "grug_level": 2,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "based-you-cant-pour-from",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best productivity hack is caring deeply about what you're working on. Everything else is optimization.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "passion",
        "intrinsic-motivation"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-productivity-hack-585",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The most underrated skill is knowing when to stop. Not everything needs to be optimized.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "stopping",
        "balance"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-most-underrated-skill",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your future self is a stranger you're building a life for. Be kind to them.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "future-self",
        "planning"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "based-your-future-self-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to plant a tree was 20 years ago. The second best time is now. Same goes for building your business.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "timing",
        "planting"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-to-588",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Rest is not the opposite of work. It's the foundation of it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "rest",
        "work"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "based-rest-is-not-the",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to build good habits is when you don't need them. The worst time is when you desperately do.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "habits",
        "proactive"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-to-590",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best meetings are the ones with clear agendas, time limits, and action items. Everything else is a waste.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business",
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "meetings",
        "efficiency"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-meetings-are-823",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "We are what we repeatedly do. Excellence, then, is not an act, but a habit.",
      "author": "Will Durant",
      "author_slug": "durant",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "habits",
        "excellence"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "durant-we-are-what-we",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best habits are the ones you don't have to think about. Make them automatic.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "habits",
        "automatic"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-habits-are",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your daily routine is your life in miniature. Design it intentionally.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "routine",
        "design"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-daily-routine-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best habits are the ones that compound. Small daily improvements lead to remarkable results.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "habits",
        "compounding"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-habits-are-928",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If you want to change your life, change your habits first. Habits are the compound interest of self-improvement.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "habits",
        "change"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-you-want-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to build a habit is to start small. Ridiculously small. Then build from there.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "habits",
        "small-steps"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-930",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your morning routine should set the tone for the day, not drain your energy before it starts.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "morning-routine",
        "energy"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-morning-routine-should",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best habits are the ones that align with your identity. You're not 'trying to write.' You're a writer.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "habits",
        "identity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-habits-are-932",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to start a habit is now. Not tomorrow. Not Monday. Now.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "habits",
        "starting"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-to-933",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your habits shape your future. Choose them wisely.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "habits",
        "future"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "based-your-habits-shape-your",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best tools are the ones you don't notice. They become extensions of your thinking.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "tools",
        "invisibility"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-tools-are",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your tools should serve you, not the other way around. If a tool adds complexity, replace it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "tools",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-tools-should-serve",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best workflow is the one that gets out of your way and lets you focus on the work.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "workflow",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-workflow-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your toolkit should be as small as possible. Each tool you add is a tool you have to learn and maintain.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "tools",
        "minimalism"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-toolkit-should-be",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to optimize your workflow is when you're doing the same thing for the third time. Automate it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "workflow",
        "automation"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-to-939",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your keyboard shortcuts are your superpowers. Learn them.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "shortcuts",
        "efficiency"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "based-your-keyboard-shortcuts-are",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best IDE is the one that disappears. You shouldn't be thinking about the tool.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity",
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "ide",
        "flow"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-ide-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your workflow should be documented. Not for others. For your future self.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "workflow",
        "documentation"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-workflow-should-be",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to automate is when you're doing the same task for the third time. The second best time is now.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "automation",
        "efficiency"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-to-943",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your workflow should be simple enough to explain in 3 steps. If not, simplify it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "workflow",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-workflow-should-be-944",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Time is what we want most, but what we use worst.",
      "author": "William Penn",
      "author_slug": "penn",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "time",
        "usage"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "penn-time-is-what-we",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to manage your time is when you have too much of it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "time-management",
        "proactive"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-to-982",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your deadline is your friend. It forces decisions. Embrace it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deadlines",
        "decisions"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-deadline-is-your",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to meet a deadline is to set intermediate deadlines. The big deadline is just a collection of small ones.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deadlines",
        "decomposition"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-984",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Parkinson's Law: work expands to fill the time available. Set shorter deadlines.",
      "author": "C. Northcote Parkinson",
      "author_slug": "parkinson",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "parkinsons-law",
        "deadlines"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "parkinson-parkinsons-law-work-expands",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best time to start a project is before you're ready. You'll never be ready.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "starting",
        "readiness"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-time-to-986",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your biggest time sink isn't meetings or email. It's context switching. Protect your focus blocks.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "context-switching",
        "focus"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-biggest-time-sink",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to get more time is to stop wasting it. Track where it goes.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "time-tracking",
        "waste"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-988",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your most productive hours are the ones you protect. Guard them ruthlessly.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "productivity",
        "protection"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-most-productive-hours",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best deadline is the one you set yourself. External deadlines are just external pressure.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deadlines",
        "self-imposed"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-deadline-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The ability to perform deep work is becoming increasingly rare at exactly the same time it is becoming increasingly valuable.",
      "author": "Cal Newport",
      "author_slug": "newport",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deep-work",
        "value"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "newport-the-ability-to-perform",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your most important work requires deep focus. Protect it like your life depends on it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deep-work",
        "protection"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-most-important-work",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to do deep work is to eliminate all distractions. Phone off. Slack closed. Door shut.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deep-work",
        "distractions"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-993",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your ability to focus is your most valuable skill. Train it like a muscle.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "focus",
        "skill"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-ability-to-focus",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best deep work happens when you're well-rested, not when you're tired. Sleep is productivity.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deep-work",
        "sleep"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-deep-work",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your focus is a finite resource. Spend it on what matters.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "focus",
        "resource"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "based-your-focus-is-a",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to improve your focus is to reduce the number of things competing for it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "focus",
        "reduction"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to-997",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Deep work is not about working harder. It's about working on the right things with full attention.",
      "author": "based",
